The Telegraph - Calcutta : International

 Friday, September 23, 2005 

 Smoking pact

 Noumea (New Caledonia), Sept. 22 (Reuters): China has signed a global treaty to reduce smoking, but it faces opposition from a state tobacco monopoly and local officials who fear a fall in tobacco profits, the World Health Organisation said today. Tobacco kills 1.2 million people a year in China, the worlds largest consumer of cigarettes.




